\c 1
\s1 Kurban bakaran
\p
\v 1 Dari dalam kemah pertemuan TUHAN memanggil Musa dan berkata kepadanya,
\v 2 "Katakan kepada orang Israel: Bila mereka ingin membawa persembahan kepada ALLAH, mereka harus mempersembahkan seekor domba,kambing atau sapi.
\p
\v 3 Jika yang kamu persembahkankan adalah seekor sapi jantan yang akan dibakar di altar, maka persembahanmu haruslah sapi jantan yang tak cacat. Kamu harus membawanya ke pintu masuk ke dalam Kemah Suci, agar persembahanmu dapat diterima oleh ALLAH.
\v 4 Kamu harus meletakkan tanganmu di korban persembahan itu. Jika kamu melakukan itu, maka ALLAH akan menerima kurban itu sebagai pengampunan atas dosa-dosa yang telah kamu lakukan.
\v 5 Kamu harus menyembelih lembu muda di depan ALLAH. Kemudian anak-anak Harun, yang adalah imam, akan membawa darah itu dan memercikkannya ke sekeliling mezbah di dekat pintu masuk Kemah Suci.
\v 6 Kamu harus menguliti binatang itu dan memotongnya menjadi beberapa bagian. Anda harus mencuci bagian dalam dan kaki banteng.
\v 7 Then Aaron's sons will put wood on the altar and light a fire.
\v 8 Then they will arrange the pieces, including the head and the fat, on the burning wood.
\v 9 Then one of the priests will completely burn all of it on the altar. And the aroma will be pleasing to Yahweh.
\p
\v 10 If you are offering a sheep or a goat, it must be a male without any defect.
\v 11 You must slaughter it in front of Yahweh, on the north side of the altar\add and drain all the blood into a bowl\add*. Then Aaron's sons will sprinkle the blood against all sides of the altar.
\v 12 You must cut the animal into pieces. You must wash the inner parts and the legs of the animal. Then the priests will arrange the pieces, including the head and the fat, on the burning wood.
\v 13 Then one of the priests will take all of it and completely burn all of it on the altar. And the aroma as it burns will be pleasing to Yahweh.
\p
\v 14 If what you are offering to Yahweh is a bird, you must offer a dove or a young pigeon.
\v 15 The priest will take it to the altar and wring/twist off its head. Then he will burn the head on the altar. He will drain out the bird's blood onto the side of the altar.
\v 16 Then he will remove the bird's ◄craw/food-grinding pouch► and what is inside it, and throw it on the east side of the altar, where the ashes are thrown.
\v 17 Then he will grasp the bird's wings and partially tear the bird open. Then he will burn it completely in the fire on the altar. And the aroma will be pleasing to Yahweh.”